<subSubSection id="CF35A94C767F4AA36589F97AF84EB127" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="6C7C5E863C06C3BFA998C3F061D55E50" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AB07F588A6514ACAA84F26149B919B1B" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">selloana: In honour of Friedrich Sellow (1789-1831), German botanist, a major collector of Brazilian flora.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A227F2D3CE3674359232D3392112BA9F" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" type="nomenclatural comments">
<paragraph id="997F7D91A4620B11AE996044E5587A70" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">Nomenclatural comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0E638B5B5E9ED965E5B02228AC471604" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">
<taxonomicName id="5122F875ABF6D2E5F57F5D12A7083B78" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Arundo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Arundo dioeca" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dioeca">Arundo dioeca</taxonomicName>
Spreng. is a later homonym of 
<taxonomicName id="0F679B2FD36DD0E3E4CD3DCBB7BA529F" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Arundo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Arundo dioica" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dioica">Arundo dioica</taxonomicName>
Lour. (1790) from Indochina, and is consequently illegitimate. 
<taxonomicName id="AEAEF71727A95407E7DFA0DE49ECC102" authorityName="Testoni &amp; Linder" authorityYear="2017" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Arundo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Arundo selloana" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="selloana">Arundo selloana</taxonomicName>
Schult. &amp; Schult.f. is a new name for 
<taxonomicName id="4A4F6A5C8BBD9236D96C8CF4D696C76C" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Arundo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Arundo dioica" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dioica">Arundo dioica</taxonomicName>
Spreng.; 
<taxonomicName id="3B49A52B3913234018A652A93A592ACA" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Arundo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Arundo dioeca" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dioeca">Arundo dioeca</taxonomicName>
Spreng. is cited in the protologue, and the diagnoses are identical. Furthermore, both description cite a Sellow collection, without number, from Montevideo. It is most likely that the type is 
<emphasis id="098835D28546F45FA0938FF3C0B566F2" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">Sellow 570</emphasis>
from Montevideo, which is in B, and is designated here as lectotype. Curiously, 
<bibRefCitation id="DD669AE7162E376504DF5C96B0AC67B9" author="Conert, J" journalOrPublisher="Cramer, Weinheim" pageId="26" pageNumber="65" refId="B5" refString="Conert, J, 1961. Die Systematik und Anatomie der Arundineae. J. Cramer, Weinheim" title="Die Systematik und Anatomie der Arundineae. J." year="1961">Conert (1961)</bibRefCitation>
proposed 
<emphasis id="B71A988C95B3F82915F79896AD6EAA2B" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">Sellow 396</emphasis>
from Brasilia as holotype of 
<taxonomicName id="0B12EBEC078D1AAA5A365FB47461C51F" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Arundo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Arundo dioica" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dioica">Arundo dioica</taxonomicName>
, although Sprengel explicitly mentions that the type is from Monte Video. 
<taxonomicName id="36014C619C209320D6CCE04C0282F09C" authorityName="Nees" authorityYear="1829" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Gynerium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Gynerium argenteum" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="argenteum">Gynerium argenteum</taxonomicName>
Nees is also based on the same collection as 
<taxonomicName id="56772788EA1DC828CFA8472DC8C4C167" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Arundo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Arundo dioica" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dioica">Arundo dioica</taxonomicName>
Spreng., plus some additional material. All three names are based on the same type.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
